subSubSection.paragraph:
Head, nape and pectoral-fin base naked; body scales mostly cycloid, except for narrow band of ctenoid scales hidden beneath depressed pectoral fin, and wedge of ctenoid scales on lateral surfaces of posterior body and caudal peduncle behind and above middle of anal fin; ctenoid scales on body each bearing 4–10 short peripheral cteni (
Roberts 1993
); ventral contour of body and isthmus fully scaled; narrow band of mostly ctenoid scales on fleshy portion of caudal-fin base; no scales on dorsal- or anal-fin bases.
